(4, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flash_game/upload/images/GT_Featurebox_Crossselling_Final.jpg" style="width: 137px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Yatzy Live', '<h3 id="a_3002" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Yatzy Live: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<strong style="font-style: inherit;">How to play&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		Details for multi-player games can be found under the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gametwist.fr/help.asp?id_topic=479&amp;xslPostFix=&amp;id_article=2865" style="color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">General Instructions</a>.<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<b>Rules</b><br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		Yatzy&nbsp;Live is a dice game for two to four&nbsp;players. The aim of the game is to use five dice to roll as many 1s, 2s, 3s, etc. as possible. Special combinations of dice (such as Straight, Full House and Yatzy) result in bonus points.<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		The dice can be rolled three times in each round. After each roll, the player is free to decide what dice to keep and which to use to keep playing. After the third toss at the latest, the points have to be entered into the table on the left.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		Each player has<b>&nbsp;three Jokers&nbsp;</b>in the game. If a player has already rolled three times in a round, the Joker can be used to&nbsp;<b>change the number&nbsp;</b>on one of the die before entering the total into the table. More than one Joker cannot be used at the same time.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		The winner is the player who combines the most effectively and has the highest total at the end of the game.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<b>Points</b><br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<b>1 to 6:&nbsp;</b><br />\r\n		These are combinations of dice with the same number. If a player rolls e.g. three 2s, he/she gets six points for the 2s-field.<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<b>Bonus:&nbsp;</b><br />\r\n		A player gets bonus points for reaching 63 or more points in the upper part of the points table (1 to 6). He/she gets a bonus of 35 points, which are added to the total score.<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<b>Three of a Kind:&nbsp;</b><br />\r\n		These are combinations of three of the same number, e.g. three 5s. The numbers on the dice are added up to calculate the score.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<b>Four of a Kind:&nbsp;</b><br />\r\n		These are combinations of four of the same number, e.g. four 5s. The numbers on the dice are added up to calculate the score.<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<b>Full House:&nbsp;</b><br />\r\n		To get a Full House, the player has to roll three of the same number and two of another, e.g. three 5s and two 3s. The player gets 25 points for a Full House.<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<b>Small Straight:&nbsp;</b><br />\r\n		The player gets 30 points for rolling four dice with consecutive values. The possibilities are 1-2-3-4, 2-3-4-5, 3-4-5-6 and any other die.<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<b>Large Straight:&nbsp;</b><br />\r\n		The player gets 40 points for rolling all five dice with consecutive values. The possibilities are 1-2-3-4-5 and 2-3-4-5-6.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Yatzy Live is a&nbsp;</span><b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">dice game</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">,</span><b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">&nbsp;</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">in which&nbsp;</span><b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">2 to 4&nbsp;players&nbsp;</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">play&nbsp;</span><b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">3 rounds&nbsp;</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">using 5 dice.&nbsp;</span><b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">The aim of the game&nbsp;</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">is to collect as many points as possible. Each player tries to roll various combinations of 1s, 2s, 3s, 4s, 5s and 6s. The points rolled have to be entered into the table after the third round at the latest. The options for entering points are highlighted in green.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">If no suitable result is rolled by the third round, it is possible to delete fields in the table or use up to three&nbsp;</span><b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Jokers&nbsp;</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">per game. A Joker allows you to click on a die until the number you require appears. The player who collects the most points by making good combinations wins.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n', '0', 3, '', 9, '', 'Yam Live', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	Yam Live: Instructions</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Comment jouer à</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Détails de jeux multi-joueurs peuvent être trouvés dans les instructions générales.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Règles</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Yam Live est un jeu de dés pour deux à quatre joueurs. Le but du jeu est d&#39;utiliser cinq dés à lancer que de nombreux 1s, 2s, 3s, etc que possible. Combinaisons spéciales de dés (comme Straight, Full House et Yam) se traduisent par des points bonus.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Les dés peuvent être enroulés trois fois à chaque tour. Après chaque lancer, le joueur est libre de décider ce dés à conserver et à utiliser pour continuer à jouer. Après le troisième tirage au sort au plus tard, les points doivent être entrées dans la table de gauche.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Chaque joueur dispose de trois jokers dans le jeu. Si un joueur a déjà lancé trois fois dans un tour, le Joker peut être utilisé pour changer le numéro d&#39;un de la filière avant d&#39;entrer dans le total dans la table. Plus d&#39;un joker ne peut pas être utilisé en même temps.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Le gagnant est le joueur qui réunit la plus efficace et a le plus grand total à la fin de la partie.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Points</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	1 à 6:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Ce sont des combinaisons de dés avec le même numéro. Si un joueur obtient par exemple trois 2, il / elle reçoit six points pour le 2s-champ.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Bonus:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Un joueur reçoit des points bonus pour atteindre 63 points ou plus dans la partie supérieure de la grille de points (1 à 6). Il / elle reçoit un bonus de 35 points, qui sont ajoutés au score total.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Three of a Kind:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Ce sont des combinaisons de trois d&#39;un même nombre, par exemple trois 5s. Les nombres sur les dés sont additionnés pour calculer le score.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Four of a Kind:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Ce sont des combinaisons de quatre du même nombre, par exemple quatre 5s. Les nombres sur les dés sont additionnés pour calculer le score.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Full House:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Pour obtenir un Full House, le joueur doit lancer trois le même nombre et deux de l&#39;autre, par exemple, trois 5s 3s et deux. Le joueur obtient 25 points pour un Full House.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Petit droite:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Le joueur reçoit 30 points pour les rouler quatre dés avec des valeurs consécutives. Les possibilités sont 1-2-3-4, 2-3-4-5, 3-4-5-6 et toute autre filière.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Grande Suite:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Le joueur reçoit 40 points pour les rouler tous les cinq dés avec des valeurs consécutives. Les possibilités sont 1-2-3-4-5 2-3-4-5-6 et.</div>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	Yam Live est un jeu de dés, dans lequel 2 à 4 joueurs jouer 3 tours en utilisant 5 dés. Le but du jeu est de collecter autant de points que possible. Chaque joueur essaie de rouler diverses combinaisons de 1s, 2s, 3s, 4s, 5s et 6s. Les points roulés doivent être entrées dans la table après le troisième tour au plus tard. Les options pour les points qui entrent sont surlignés en vert.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Si aucun résultat convenable est laminée par le troisième tour, il est possible de supprimer des champs dans le tableau ou utiliser jusqu&#39;à trois jokers par match. Un Joker vous permet de cliquer sur une matrice jusqu&#39;à ce que le numéro de votre correspondant s&#39;affiche. Le joueur qui a le plus de points en faisant de bonnes combinaisons gagne.</div>\r\n', '0'),
(5, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flash_game/upload/images/game_109_logo_137x77_EN-US.png" style="width: 137px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Bingo', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_4163" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Bingo: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			In the Bingo lobby players can decide to play at either a 75-Ball table or 90-Ball table. It is not possible to set up new tables. Simply click on &ldquo;Enter&rdquo; to join the desired table.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Bingo cards are displayed on the playing field. All 60 Bingo cards can be viewed using the scroll bar. Select a card by clicking on it, then click &lsquo;Buy&rsquo; to purchase it. It is also possible to select more than one card at once by using the &ldquo;Card Selector&rdquo; option. The &ldquo;Card Selector&rdquo; can be set to a number from 1 to 60, allowing the player to mark the corresponding number of cards. For example, if the &ldquo;Card Selector&rdquo; is set to 10, 10 playing cards will be marked.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			By clicking on &ldquo;New&rdquo; the cards, which have neither been marked nor bought, are replaced by new cards.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Alternatively, players can use the &ldquo;Auto-Buy&rdquo; function. Clicking on this button opens a new window, where the player can select how many cards he/she wishes to have and for how many rounds, e.g.: 10 rounds with 5 cards each. The entered number of cards shall then be bought automatically at the start of each round.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The &ldquo;Auto-Sorting&rdquo; function can be toggled during the draw. This function orders the player&rsquo;s cards according to how close the card is to being completed. This is on at the start of the game by default.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Clicking on the &ldquo;Bingo&rdquo; button announces that you have achieved &lsquo;Bingo&rsquo;. Should you forget to click on the button, your winnings shall be awarded regardless. If a player loses his/her connection to the game before clicking on &ldquo;Bingo&rdquo;, the win will also be valid.</p>\r\n		<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Rules</h3>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			There are two variations of Bingo to choose from: 75-Ball and 90-Ball. Up to 50 players can play at one table. The aim of the game is to form a specific pattern on the Bingo card by crossing out the drawn numbers. The player, who first forms the corresponding pattern, wins and the round comes to an end.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<b>75-Ball Bingo</b></p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			In this version of the game, the field measures 5 by 5, filled with numbers from 1 to 75. The player who wins the round wins the pot.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<b>90-Ball Bingo</b></p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			In this version of the game, the field measures 9 by 3. Per line, 5 numbers ranging from 1 to 90 are shown. There are three ways to win. The first is by completing a row, meaning that all 5 numbers in any of the rows on a card are marked off. The second way is by completing 2 such rows. The main way to win comes when all 15 numbers on a card are marked off (a &ldquo;Full House&rdquo;). In the 90-Ball variation, the pot is divided according to a predefined formula.</p>\r\n		<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Order of play</h3>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Bingo basically consists of two phases: the purchase phase and the draw phase. The game begins with the purchase phase. This lasts 90 seconds. During this time the players can select and purchase the desired number of Bingo cards. Players can buy cards as often as they wish within the given time limit. Each card costs a defined amount. The player&rsquo;s stake is therefore the sum of cards bought, multiplied by the stake per card. A share of the stake is added to the pot, while the rest constitutes the operating fee.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The draw phase follows. Every player, who has purchased at least one card, takes part in the draw. Only the purchased cards will then be displayed in the playing field. If a player didn&rsquo;t buy any cards for the game, he/she has the opportunity to buy cards for the next round. For the players involved in the game, one number after the next is drawn. The drawn numbers, providing they are shown on the card(s), are marked off. As soon as the round has been won, the winner is announced and the next purchase phase can begin.</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Bingo&nbsp;</strong>is played and loved the world over. Although there are many different variations, the general order of play is always the same. At GameTwist players have the opportunity to select between 1 and 60 Bingo cards, giving them a higher chance of winning.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The following variations are available: 75-Ball and 90-Ball.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Up to 50 players may play at a single Bingo table. The aim of the game is to mark off a certain pattern on the Bingo card with the numbers drawn at random. The player to achieve this first wins and the round comes to an end.</p>\r\n', '0', 4, '', 8, '', '', '', '', ''),
(6, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flash_game/upload/images/game_53_logo_137x77_EN-US.png" style="width: 137px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', '8-Ball Pool', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_1214" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	8-Ball Pool: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			<br />\r\n			How to play</h3>\r\n		A cue appears when you click on the white ball. In front of the cue you will see a yellow line with an image of the white ball. This shows the direction of the shot. You can rotate the cue in the desired direction by moving the mouse while holding down the left mouse button. The power of the shot will be shown by changes in the length of an arrow. Once you let go of the mouse button, the white ball is played. Spin on the ball only has an effect if the ball hits a cushion. In the upper left-hand corner of the table you will see a display indicating which ball&nbsp;is being played by the current player and how many balls still have to be potted.\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n		<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Rules</h3>\r\n		This is a pool game for two players. A total of 16 balls are used, seven solid and seven striped, as well as one black and one white ball. The player who opens the game starts. Before the start of the game, the ball can be placed anywhere in the left quadrant. Once a ball is&nbsp;potted (except during the opening shot or a foul), this decides who plays solids and who plays stripes. From this point on, players may only play balls with their own pattern. As long as a player keeps potting his/her own balls, he/she may continue playing.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		A player commits a&nbsp;<b>foul&nbsp;</b>when&nbsp;\r\n		<ul style="margin: 1em 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px;">\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				he/she pots the white ball</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				plays no ball or the wrong ball&nbsp;</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				pots the black ball prematurely&nbsp;</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				less than four coloured balls touch the edges or none are&nbsp;potted during the break&nbsp;</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				after the first contact between the white ball and another ball no balls are&nbsp;potted or not even one touches a cushion</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<br />\r\n			The player who&nbsp;wins the foul can place the white ball anywhere on the&nbsp;table and continue playing.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<b>The&nbsp;aim of the game&nbsp;</b>is to&nbsp;pot your own balls in as few rounds as possible. Finally, the black ball also has to be&nbsp;potted in the correct pocket. The first player to correctly&nbsp;pot all seven of his or her balls and then the black ball wins. If a player causes a round to end prematurely, the opponent wins. A game ends in a draw if neither player is able to pot a ball after 20 shots.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n		<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Points</h3>\r\n		No points are given in 8-Ball Billiards. Only games won or lost are counted.&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>8-Ball Pool&nbsp;</strong>is the classic pool game. So sit back and take on opponents online at GameTwist. In 8-Ball Billiards two players play against one another.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	There is a total of 16 balls: 7 solids, 7 striped, 1 white and one black ball.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	As soon as the first ball has been potted the players are assigned their balls &ndash; either solid or striped. Using the white ball, the players must attempt to pot all of their balls. Once this is achieved they must pot the black in a certain pocket.</p>\r\n', '0', 5, '', 31, '', '', '', '', ''),
