(25, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/nguoi_phu_nu_suot_doi_gap_may_man_lam_phat_sot_cu_dan_mang20130122150225.jpg" style="width: 116px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Snooker', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_1175" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n	Snooker: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n			How to play</h3>\r\n		<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">This game is a variant of billiards, designed for two players. The object is to alternately play red and coloured balls in order to win the most points. At the start of the game there are 22 balls on the table, 15 red (one point each), 6 coloured (yellow=2 points, green=3 points, brown= 4 points, blue= 5 points, pink= 6 points and black= 7 points) and one white ball. The break is made from the &bdquo;D&ldquo; (a mark on the table in the shape of a D).&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n		<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n		<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">If you click next to the white ball, an arrow will appear which you can use to determine the direction of the shot. The magnitude of the shot is shown by changes in the length of the arrow. Above and below the table you will see notices of which ball is being played and whose player&rsquo;s turn it is.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n		<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n		<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">The game is over once all red and coloured balls have been sunk. The player with the most points wins.</span></div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Snooker&nbsp;</strong>is a variation of pool, in which two players play against one another. The game starts with 22 balls on the table.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	15 of the balls are red (and are worth one point each), 6 are coloured (yellow = 2 points, green = 3 points, brown = 4 points, blue = 5 points, pink = 6 points and black = 7 points) and the white ball is called the cue ball.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The players must first attempt to pot a red using the white ball. If a player achieves this without giving away a foul, he/she must choose a coloured ball and attempt to pot it. If the player achieves this, again without giving away a foul, he/she must target another red. This pattern continues until a foul occurs, at which point the opponent may take his/her turn.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Players receive points for every ball potted. These are added together during the game and the player with the highest total at the end is the winner.</p>\r\n', '0', 5, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(26, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/9.jpg" style="width: 137px; height: 74px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Football', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_1160" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Mowing Madness: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">How to play&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Simply click on &ldquo;New Game&rdquo; to start a new game, and choose, amongst other options, the maximum skill level of your opponent. Alternatively you may join a game that has been started by another player.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			This game puts you in the shoes of a groundsman, whose duty it is to mow the football pitch perched on top of a tractor. Patches of the pitch are mown by driving over them with the tractor. The tractor can be directed by using the arrow keys and made to jump by pressing the space bar.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Starting on Level 1, you must successfully mow the entire pitch before you may progress to the next. There are 3 levels in total.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Mowing Madness is a two-player duel.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			- Both players start in the same position and are subject to the same conditions.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			- Players may play consecutive games.<br />\r\n			- Once a player has completed a game, s/he may either watch his/her opponent, or leave the game and start a new game.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			- Other players may be directly invited to play a game.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Rules</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Two players play against each other in this game. At the start of the game, each player is shown the football pitch. Stepping into the shoes of the groundsman, the players must mow the pitch with a tractor, whilst two teams are playing a game of football!&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The objective of the game is to mow as much of the pitch as possible and therefore score the most points. The winner of the game is the player with the highest points total.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The game ends when the time limit is reached, or when the player has lost all of his/her lives. Each player starts with 3 lives. One life is lost if the player collides with one of the footballers. However, you may gain extra lives &ndash; see &ldquo;Points&rdquo;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class="contBox" style="margin: 0px; padding: 10px;">\r\n	<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 10px; overflow: hidden;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n			<span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial;"><o:p></o:p></span>&nbsp;This game puts you in the shoes of a groundsman, whose duty it is to mow the football pitch perched on top of a tractor. Patches of the pitch are mown by driving over them with the tractor. The tractor can be directed by using the arrow keys and made to jump by pressing the space bar.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Starting on Level 1, you must successfully mow the entire pitch before you may progress to the next. There are 3 Levels in total. Mowing Madness is a two-player duel.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The objective of the game is to mow as much of the pitch as possible and therefore score the most points. The winner of the game is the player who reaches the highest points total. The game ends when the time limit is reached, or when the player has lost all of his/her lives. Each player starts with 3 lives.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '0', 5, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(27, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/8.jpg" style="width: 137px; height: 74px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Jolly', '<h3 id="a_4106" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Jolly: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			A new game can be started by simply clicking &quot;New Game&quot;. The player may then define a number of settings to determine who may join the game and the opponents&rsquo; skill level. It must also be decided how many points are to be played to &ndash; 50, 100 or 200 points. Alternatively, a player is free to join a game that has already been set up by an opponent.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			An exclamation mark signifies that it is the player&rsquo;s turn, while an arrow points at the opponent who is making his/her move.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The time remaining for the move is shown to the right of the table, as is the agreed maximum point total and other handy buttons such as &ldquo;Player Info.&rdquo; and &ldquo;Invite&rdquo;. The game chat is also located here.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The player&rsquo;s own cards are shown face-up and his/her nickname and point total are displayed below. At the top left of the screen are two piles of cards. The pile facing upwards is the discard pile, while the other is the deck. In the discard pile, the cards are laid next to each other, as, later in the game, these may be picked up by certain players &ndash; namely once they have laid cards for the first time. To take a card from the deck, the player need only click on the deck itself and the card will be added to the hand. Should a player wish to take a card from the discard pile, it may be that more than one card is picked up, as it depends on the position of the desired card. If the player clicks on the first card in the pile, just that card will be added to the hand. However, if the player clicks on the 5th card, all five will be added to the hand.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			To lay a card on the discard pile, the player can either click on the unwanted card or drag and drop it onto the pile. Jokers can normally only be discarded or laid on the table by dragging and dropping.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Each player is shown a blended out &ldquo;Lay Cards&rdquo; button. As soon as the player has formed a group or sequence that can be laid, this button becomes active. The group or sequence that can be laid is highlighted by a blue line that stretches across all of the cards.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The laid cards are shown in the middle of the table. To add cards to a group or sequence already laid, a player need only drag and drop the desired card into position. To make the order of the cards clear, green arrows show the ends of the groups and sequences.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Each player has the oppo</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Jolly&nbsp;</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">is a card game for two to four players and is played with two 52-card decks and six jokers. At the start of the game each player receives 13 cards. The remaining cards form the deck. There is no set number of rounds, as a defined point target must be reached over the course of the game (100, 125, 150, 175, 200, 225, 250, 300, 350, 400, 450 or 500 points).</span></p>\r\n<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	The aim of the game is to form combinations with the hand cards and score as many points as possible when laying them. The combinations can be either groups (three or four cards of the same value, but different suits) or sequences (at least three like-suit, consecutive cards).</div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<br />\r\n	The game includes jokers, whereby the jokers can take the place of any card in a combination. However two jokers cannot be used consecutively in a sequence.</div>\r\n', '0', 2, '', 0, '', 'Gai', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	Jolly: Instructions</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Un nouveau jeu peut être lancé en cliquant simplement sur &quot;New Game&quot;. Le joueur peut alors définir un certain nombre de paramètres pour déterminer qui peut rejoindre le jeu et le niveau de compétence de l&#39;équipe adverse. Il faut également décidé combien de points doivent être joués à - 50 points, 100 ou 200. Alternativement, un joueur est libre d&#39;adhérer à un jeu qui a déjà été mis en place par un adversaire.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Un point d&#39;exclamation signifie que c&#39;est au tour du joueur, tandis qu&#39;une flèche pointe vers l&#39;adversaire qui en est à sa / son déménagement.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Le temps restant pour le déménagement est indiqué à droite de la table, comme c&#39;est le plafond annuel convenu de points total et autres boutons pratiques telles que &quot;Infos joueur.&quot; Et &quot;Inviter&quot;. Le chat jeu se trouve également ici.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Propres cartes du joueur sont affichés face vers le haut et sa / son pseudo et total de points sont affichés ci-dessous. En haut à gauche de l&#39;écran se trouvent deux piles de cartes. La pile est orientée vers le haut de la pile d&#39;écart, tandis que l&#39;autre est le platine. Dans la pile de défausse, les cartes sont posées côte à côte, comme plus tard dans le jeu, ceux-ci peuvent être captés par certains acteurs - à savoir une fois qu&#39;ils ont établi des cartes pour la première fois. Pour prendre une carte de la pioche, le joueur suffit de cliquer sur le pont lui-même et la carte sera ajouté à la main. Si un joueur souhaite prendre une carte de la défausse, il se peut que plus d&#39;une carte est ramassé, car elle dépend de la position de la carte désirée. Si le joueur clique sur la première carte de la pile, juste que la carte sera ajouté à la main. Cependant, si le joueur clique sur la 5ème carte, tous les cinq seront ajoutés à la main.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Pour poser une carte sur la pile de défausse, le joueur peut soit cliquer sur la carte indésirables ou faites glisser et déposez-le sur la pile. Jokers ne peut normalement être jeté ou mis sur la table par glisser-déposer.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Chaque joueur reçoit un mélange des &quot;Lay Cartes&quot; bouton. Dès que le joueur a formé un groupe ou une séquence qui peut être posé, ce bouton devient actif. Le groupe ou une séquence qui peut être fixé est mis en évidence par une ligne bleue qui s&#39;étend sur toutes les cartes.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Les cartes dressées sont indiqués dans le milieu de la table. Pour ajouter des cartes à un groupe ou une séquence déjà posé, un joueur suffit de glisser et déposer la carte désirée en position. Pour rendre l&#39;ordre des cartes claires, des flèches vertes indiquent les extrémités des groupes et des séquences.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Chaque joueur dispose de l&#39;oppo</div>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	Jolly est un jeu de cartes pour deux à quatre joueurs et se joue avec deux de 52 cartes et six jokers. Au début du jeu, chaque joueur reçoit 13 cartes. Les cartes restantes forment la pioche. Il n&#39;ya pas de nombre défini de tours, comme une cible ponctuelle définie doit être atteint au cours du jeu (100, 125, 150, 175, 200, 225, 250, 300, 350, 400, 450 ou 500 points).</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Le but du jeu est de former des combinaisons avec les cartes en main et marquer autant de points que possible lors de leur pose. Les combinaisons peuvent être soit des groupes (trois ou quatre cartes de la même valeur, mais combinaisons différentes) ou des séquences (au moins trois comme-suit, cartes consécutives).</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Le jeu comprend jokers, où les jokers peuvent prendre la place de n&#39;importe quelle carte dans une combinaison. Cependant, deux jokers ne peuvent pas être utilisés consécutivement dans une séquence.</div>\r\n', '0'),
(28, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/4973-featurebox_twists-shop.jpg" style="width: 214px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Solitaire', '<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: italic;">How to play</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	A game can be opened by clicking the button &quot;New Game&quot;. The player who opened the game can set the maximum skill level of the desired opponent.&nbsp;He/she is also free to participate in a game already opened by another player.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	Cards can be moved to a target pile by dragging them using the left mouse button. If this move is not possible the card automatically moves back to the original pile. To move several cards, simply select the highest one.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	You can turn over a card by clicking on it. A click on a card which is already face up moves it to a possible location (if there are several options, one is selected at random).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	To the right of the game table are two buttons. When activated, the first option turns cards over automatically, while the second places cards (when possible) into the suit positions above. Both options can be toggled independently of one another.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Solitaire is played as a duel. The following rules apply:</strong></p>\r\n<ul style="margin: 1em 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		Both players start out the same and receive the same cards per round.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		Players can also play consecutively.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		After you finish your game, you can watch your opponent, leave the table or even start a new round.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		It is possible to invite other players, but opening private tables is not allowed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Solitaire</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">&nbsp;- also known as patience, is one of the most popular card games worldwide. Our variant is played as a duel between two players. Players aim to group all 54 cards in 4 sequences of cards in descending order (King - 1). Both players are issued the same card arrangement and therefore have the same chance of winning.</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">The game starts off with seven stacks of cards face-up. Extra cards form a draw pile of cards face-down. The player draws a card from the draw pile, exposes it and then attempts to place the card on one of the seven stacks. To be able to place a card on a stack, the draw card must follow the descending order of the card on top of a pile (leading card) and its colour must also oppose that of the leading card. For example - a player can only place a 7 of hearts or diamonds (red) on a pile led by a 8 of spades or clubs (black). If this is not possible, the player draws the next card from the draw pile and makes a new attempt. When the player exhausts the draw pile, the exhausted draw cards are rotated and the player may attempt to place the draw cards again. Rotation of the draw pile represents a new round. Players lose points for every new round he/she begins.</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">The aim of&nbsp;</span><b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">solitaire</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">&nbsp;is to hold the most points at the end of each game. Players can opt to end the game at any time, should he/she be unable to make any senseful move.</span></p>\r\n', '0', 2, '', 0, '', 'Solitaire', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	Comment jouer à</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Un jeu peut être ouvert en cliquant sur le bouton &quot;New Game&quot;. Le joueur qui a ouvert le jeu peut régler le niveau de compétence maximum de l&#39;adversaire souhaité. Il / elle est également libre de participer à un jeu déjà ouvert par un autre joueur.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Les cartes peuvent être déplacés vers une pile cible en les faisant glisser avec le bouton gauche de la souris. Si ce mouvement n&#39;est pas possible, la carte revient automatiquement à la pile d&#39;origine. Pour déplacer plusieurs cartes, il suffit de sélectionner le plus élevé.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Vous pouvez retourner une carte en cliquant dessus. Un clic sur une carte qui est déjà face vers le haut il se déplace à un endroit possible (si il ya plusieurs options, l&#39;un est choisi au hasard).</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	A droite de la table de jeu se trouvent deux boutons. Lorsqu&#39;elle est activée, la première option s&#39;avère cartes automatiquement le relais, tandis que les deuxièmes cartes lieux (si possible) dans les positions costume ci-dessus. Les deux options peuvent être activées indépendamment l&#39;un de l&#39;autre.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Solitaire se joue en duel. Les règles suivantes s&#39;appliquent:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Les deux joueurs commencent la même chose et recevoir les mêmes cartes par tour.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Les joueurs peuvent également jouer consécutivement.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Une fois que vous avez terminé votre jeu, vous pouvez regarder votre adversaire, quitter la table ou même de commencer un nouveau cycle.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Il est possible d&#39;inviter d&#39;autres joueurs, mais l&#39;ouverture des tables privées n&#39;est pas autorisée.</div>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	Solitaire - également connu comme la patience, est l&#39;un des jeux de cartes les plus populaires au monde. Notre variante se joue comme un duel entre deux joueurs. Les joueurs visent à regrouper l&#39;ensemble de 54 cartes en 4 séquences de cartes dans l&#39;ordre décroissant (King - 1). Les deux joueurs sont émis l&#39;arrangement même carte et donc avoir la même chance de gagner.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Le jeu commence avec sept piles de cartes face visible. Des cartes supplémentaires former une pioche de cartes face cachée. Le joueur tire une carte de la pioche, il expose et tente ensuite de placer la carte sur l&#39;une des sept piles. Pour être en mesure de placer une carte sur une pile, la carte de tirage doit suivre l&#39;ordre décroissant de la carte sur le dessus d&#39;une pile (carte de gauche) et sa couleur doit également s&#39;opposer à celle de la carte principale. Par exemple - un joueur ne peut placer un 7 de coeur ou de diamants (rouge) sur une pile dirigée par un 8 de pique ou de clubs (noir). Si cela n&#39;est pas possible, le joueur tire la carte suivante de la pioche et fait une nouvelle tentative. Lorsque le joueur épuise la pioche, les cartes tirage épuisées sont en rotation et le joueur peut tenter de placer les cartes de tirage à nouveau. La rotation de la pioche représente un nouveau cycle. Les joueurs perdent des points pour chaque nouveau cycle, il / elle commence.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Le but du solitaire est de tenir le plus de points à la fin de chaque match. Les joueurs peuvent choisir de terminer le jeu à n&#39;importe quel moment, si il / elle est incapable de faire aucun mouvement senseful.</div>\r\n', '0'),
(29, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/app_ios.png" style="width: 231px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Tarot', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	French Tarot is a challenging card game which requires players to exercise great skill and tactical play. Played since the middle ages, it is often referred to as &quot;the game of kings&quot;. It is intended for 4 players and uses a deck of 78 cards. Along with the 4 classic suits (Hearts, Diamonds, Clubs and Spades), there are 21 numbered trump cards - with the 21 being the highest trump card and 1 the lowest - and 1 special &quot;Excuse&quot; (or &quot;Fool&quot;) card.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	French Tarot is a team game that also features &quot;lone fighter&quot; or solo game elements. An individual can play against a team formed by the other three players for the trick. The tables can turn in the next round, as the solo player becomes a part of the team and one of the former team members becomes the solo player.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	And a point worth noting: Tarot was mentioned in Italian scripts originating from the 15th century!<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<b>Aims of the game</b><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul style="margin: 1em 1em 1em 11px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		Take as many tricks as possible to win the game.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		Get as many Oudlers in the tricks won as possible.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		The declarer aims to score as many points as set in the contract. Opponents attempt to prevent the declarer from reaching his/her goal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	French Tarot is a challenging card game which requires players to exercise great skill and tactical play. Played since the middle ages, it is often referred to as &quot;the game of kings&quot;. It is intended for 4 players and uses a deck of 78 cards. Along with the 4 classic suits (Hearts, Diamonds, Clubs and Spades), there are 21 numbered trump cards - with the 21 being the highest trump card and 1 the lowest - and 1 special &quot;Excuse&quot; (or &quot;Fool&quot;) card.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	French Tarot is a team game that also features &quot;lone fighter&quot; or solo game elements. An individual can play against a team formed by the other three players for the trick. The tables can turn in the next round, as the solo player becomes a part of the team and one of the former team members becomes the solo player.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	And a point worth noting: Tarot was mentioned in Italian scripts originating from the 15th century!<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<b>Aims of the game</b><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul style="margin: 1em 1em 1em 11px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		Take as many tricks as possible to win the game.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		Get as many Oudlers in the tricks won as possible.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		The declarer aims to score as many points as set in the contract. Opponents attempt to prevent the declarer from reaching his/her goal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '0', 2, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(30, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/payment_28_logo_90x50.png" style="width: 137px; height: 76px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Boule', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_3264" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Boule: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			How to play</h4>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			All details about how to play multiplayer games can be found in the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gametwist.fr/help.asp?id_topic=479&amp;xslPostFix=&amp;id_article=2865" style="color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">general instructions</a>.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			By clicking on the playing field and drawing the mouse back, you can determine the direction and power of the throw. Releasing the mouse button releases the ball.</p>\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Rules</h4>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Boule can be played by 2 or 3 players in direct competition. The aim of the game is to get your balls closer to the jack than your opponent(s).</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			At the start of the game the playing surface is chosen at random (sand, earth or grass) and the obstacles (such as water and hills) are placed. A player is then selected to throw the jack. If the jack lands too close to the player or out of bounds, the throw must be taken again. If the player fails to make a valid throw three times, the duty of throwing the jack passes to the next player.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			By clicking on the playing field and drawing the mouse back, you can determine the direction and power of the throw. A power bar below the playing field displays the strength of the throw. Ahead of the throw you can also determine the pitch by adjusting the arrow to the bottom left of the playing field. The flight of the throw in accordance with the power and pitch are displayed when taking the throw itself. Releasing the mouse button releases the ball.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Once the jack has been thrown, the next player takes his/her first throw, attempting to get the ball as close to the jack as possible. All of the players must have thrown one ball before the player, who is furthest from the jack must throw again.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The round comes to an end once all of the balls have been thrown. Only the player, whose ball is closest to the jack at the end of the round, scores points. One point is awarded for every ball, which is closer to the jack than any of the opponent&rsquo;s balls.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The winner of the round throws the jack at the</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_3264" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Boule: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 