(33, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/8.jpg" style="width: 137px; height: 74px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Yatzy', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_4121" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Yatzy: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<b><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Yatzy&nbsp;</span></b><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">is a game for two to four players. A player has the option of participating in a game opened by another player or by opening a game of his/her own. If you wish to take part in a game opened by another player, click on the &quot;Play&quot; button in that player&rsquo;s box. If you wish to open a game of your own, click on the button &quot;New Game&quot;. A small window will appear in which you can set the maximum skill level of your opponent(s) using a&nbsp;slider.<o:p></o:p></span>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">After rolling you can either roll the dice again or put aside some or all of the dice in the tray at the lower edge of the table. If you wish to put aside several dice after a toss, you can either drag them into the tray or simply double-click on them.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 13px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;">After each round points must be entered into a table. The options for entering points are highlighted in green. When you click on them, they are entered automatically. You can also delete fields if you are not satisfied with the result. Simply click on the empty space in the table, and a red X will appear.</span></p>\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Rules</h4>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 13px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;">This is a dice game, in which the&nbsp;aim is to roll as many 1s, 2s, 6s, etc. as possible, in five tosses over three rounds. Special combinations of dice (such as a Straight, Full House and&nbsp;Yatzy) result in bonus points. There are Classic and Live versions of the game. In the Classic version the players take turns in rolling and are shown different results. In the Live version all of the players roll at the same time and all of the players receive the same result from the dice roll</span>.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">The object of the game is to collect as many points as possible. After the third toss, at the latest, points have to be entered into&nbsp;the table. After each toss, players decide what dice to keep and which to use to keep playing. The player who makes the best combinations and thus wins the most points wins the game.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 13px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;">Each player has three Jokers. Once a player has tossed three times, he/she has the option of playing a Joker. In doing this he/she can change the result of a die to whatever is required. Jokers may only be used one at a time</span>.</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_4121" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Yatzy: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<b><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Yatzy&nbsp;</span></b><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">is a game for two to four players. A player has the option of participating in a game opened by another player or by opening a game of his/her own. If you wish to take part in a game opened by another player, click on the &quot;Play&quot; button in that player&rsquo;s box. If you wish to open a game of your own, click on the button &quot;New Game&quot;. A small window will appear in which you can set the maximum skill level of your opponent(s) using a&nbsp;slider.<o:p></o:p></span>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">After rolling you can either roll the dice again or put aside some or all of the dice in the tray at the lower edge of the table. If you wish to put aside several dice after a toss, you can either drag them into the tray or simply double-click on them.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 13px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;">After each round points must be entered into a table. The options for entering points are highlighted in green. When you click on them, they are entered automatically. You can also delete fields if you are not satisfied with the result. Simply click on the empty space in the table, and a red X will appear.</span></p>\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Rules</h4>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 13px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;">This is a dice game, in which the&nbsp;aim is to roll as many 1s, 2s, 6s, etc. as possible, in five tosses over three rounds. Special combinations of dice (such as a Straight, Full House and&nbsp;Yatzy) result in bonus points. There are Classic and Live versions of the game. In the Classic version the players take turns in rolling and are shown different results. In the Live version all of the players roll at the same time and all of the players receive the same result from the dice roll</span>.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">The object of the game is to collect as many points as possible. After the third toss, at the latest, points have to be entered into&nbsp;the table. After each toss, players decide what dice to keep and which to use to keep playing. The player who makes the best combinations and thus wins the most points wins the game.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 13px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;">Each player has three Jokers. Once a player has tossed three times, he/she has the option of playing a Joker. In doing this he/she can change the result of a die to whatever is required. Jokers may only be used one at a time</span>.</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '0', 3, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(34, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/game_8_logo_220x100_EN-US.png" style="width: 220px; height: 100px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Mahjong', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_4124" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Mahjong: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		You can start a new game by either clicking the button &quot;New Game&quot;, or by joining a game which has already been opened by another player. When you click on &quot;New Game&quot;, you can decide the maximum skill level of your opponent and the arrangement of tiles. You can choose from three options: Turtle, Aquarius and Ying Yang.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		Tiles can be removed from the game by clicking them away with the mouse. You have to click two tiles with the same symbol in order to remove them. However, the tiles may not be covered by any other tiles, either completely or partially. Moreover, a tile may not be blocked to the left or right by another tile. One side always has to be free.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		The tiles are covered in various symbols. These can be Characters, Bamboos, Circles, Dragons and Winds. There are also sets of bonus tiles, consisting of four tiles each. Their symbols are Seasons and Flowers. Moreover, all tiles are labelled with numbers and letters in order to aid orientation.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		A click on the Help button switches the&nbsp;marking function on&nbsp;or off. The first tile the player clicks on turns red. The marking function then marks all tiles which match. These are marked green. The player can now decide which tile pair to click away. Using this function does not cost you any points, but you also do not get a bonus for switching it off. You can switch the select function on or off as often as you like during the course of a game.\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			You can reverse your last move by clicking Undo, but this costs you penalty points. You can also use the Shuffle button to re-arrange the tiles, but this also costs penalty points. This function is especially useful when there are no more possible moves left. The Finish button can be used to quit the game if it is no longer possible to keep playing.</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Mahjong&nbsp;</strong>is an ancient Chinese board game played with 144 stones (Bamboo, Characters, Coins, Winds, Flowers, Seasons and Dragons). The game is played as a duel.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The aim of the game is to match like stones, remove them from the game and collect points. Stones can only be removed if they are not covered by other stones and have at least one side free. Should you need a hint to find the next pair of stones, you can click on the Help button.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	No points are deducted for activating or deactivating the Help button. If no further moves are possible you can mix up the tiles. For doing this a number of points are deducted. The same applies for undoing a move. The player with the highest score at the end of the game wins.</p>\r\n', '0', 3, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(35, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/app_ios.png" style="width: 135px; height: 45px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Reversello', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_1250" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Reversello: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			A new game can be opened simply by clicking on &quot;New Game&quot;. The player can then choose who may join the game (Any, Friends, Invited) as well as the skill level of the opponent.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			One piece is placed on the board each turn. &quot;Locking in&quot; your opponent&#39;s pieces lets you change their colour into yours. You can &quot;lock in&quot; any number of your opponent&#39;s pieces in any direction (vertically, horizontally, diagonally).&nbsp; If a player cannot lock in an opponent&#39;s piece, he/she has to wait a turn.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Rules&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			This is a game for two players. A player has either black or white pieces, which are placed on the board.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The&nbsp;aim of the game is to have the most pieces of your own colour on the board at the end of the game. The player with the most pieces wins.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The game is over when neither of the players can place a piece on the board, or there are no more unoccupied spaces on the board.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<b>Points</b></p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			In Reversello, there are no points. Only the&nbsp;number of white and black&nbsp;pieces on the board count.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<b><span style="font-size: 9pt;">Reversello</span></b><span style="font-size: 9pt;">&nbsp;is a very popular board game at GameTwist. You must employ tactics and skill to win control of all of the stones.</span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 9pt;">Two players play against each other and take it in turn to try to surround their opponent&rsquo;s stones with their own. If you achieve this, your opponent&rsquo;s stone will take on the colour of your stones. Only one stone can be placed per move.</span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 9pt;">The aim of the game is to convert all of the stones to your own colour.</span></div>\r\n', '0', 3, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(37, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/payment_28_logo_90x50.png" style="width: 137px; height: 76px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Backgammon', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	How to play</h3>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	The Backgammon lobby is different to&nbsp;the others on the platform&nbsp;in that&nbsp;players can use tabs to&nbsp;switch between the Beginners&#39; room, the Professionals&#39; room&nbsp;and the Tournament&nbsp;room. The &quot;Tournament&quot; tab only appears when a tournament is&nbsp;due to take place. The player can use a drop-down menu to select which tables are shown: all tables or only table with free seats.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	A number of important buttons are displayed above the tabs: the settings button (to change the board settings) as well as the button to toggle the game sounds. Next to these is the question mark button, which explains the symbols, and the leave button.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	Under the list of the players in the lobby are the familiar buttons: &quot;Player Info.&quot;, &quot;Ignore&quot;, &quot;Add Friend&quot; and &quot;Invite&quot;.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	A new game can be opened by clicking the button &ldquo;New Game&ldquo;. A player can select the maximum skill level of his/her opponent, in addition to other settings. A player can also choose to participate in a game which another player has already opened.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	When opening or joining a game, the player must select one of 3 modes or be aware of which mode the opponent has selected. The following modes are available:</p>\r\n<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	1. Quick Game</h4>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	In a quick game, the time limit for your move is greatly reduced. Each player is given just 30 seconds for the first move. While that move is being made, the clock shall count down. Providing the player completes his/her move within 10 seconds, an extra 10 seconds are granted for the next move (this is added to the remaining time on the clock). The maximum time limit is 30 seconds.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	For example, if a player needs 15 seconds for his/her first move, he/she shall then have just 15 seconds for&nbsp;the next move. However, should the player&nbsp;manage to complete the next move in just 5 seconds, he/she shall have 20 seconds for the next move, not 10 seconds (10 seconds of remaining time + 10 bonus seconds).</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	For quick games, it is advisable to activate the &ldquo;Automatic Roll&rdquo; function to save valuable time. For this reason, the &ldquo;Automatic Roll&rdquo; button will blink during the game until the player clicks it to activate the function. The &ldquo;Automatic Roll&rdquo; function is explained below.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	Should the connection to the server be lost during a game, the rules under &ldquo;Loss of connection for multiplayer games&rdquo; take effect.</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Backgammon&nbsp;</strong>is one of the oldest board games in the world. The game consists of a board that is divided up into 4 areas: the white home board, the white outer board, the black outer board and the black home board. Each of the sections consists of 6 triangles.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Two players play the game against one another, taking turns to roll 2 six-sided dice. Each player has 15 stones, either black or white. The aim of the game is for the players to move their pieces in accordance with the result of the dice roll into their respective home boards. A stone cannot be moved to a space already occupied by more than one stone belonging to the opponent. You can, however, move a stone onto a space occupied by a single stone belonging to the opponent. Doing this leads to your opponent&rsquo;s stone being moved to the bar (the centre of the board). The opponent must bring this stone back into play before he/she can move any other stones.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Once all of your stones are in your home board, you can start to remove them from play &ndash; this is called &lsquo;bearing off&rsquo;. The first player to bear off all of his/her stones wins the game.</p>\r\n', '0', 2, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(38, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/game_97_logo_137x77_EN-US.png" style="width: 137px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Solitaire', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	How to play</h3>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	A game can be opened by clicking the button &quot;New Game&quot;. The player who opened the game can set the maximum skill level of the desired opponent.&nbsp;He/she is also free to participate in a game already opened by another player.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	Cards can be moved to a target pile by dragging them using the left mouse button. If this move is not possible the card automatically moves back to the original pile. To move several cards, simply select the highest one.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	You can turn over a card by clicking on it. A click on a card which is already face up moves it to a possible location (if there are several options, one is selected at random).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	To the right of the game table are two buttons. When activated, the first option turns cards over automatically, while the second places cards (when possible) into the suit positions above. Both options can be toggled independently of one another.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Solitaire is played as a duel. The following rules apply:</strong></p>\r\n<ul style="margin: 1em 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		Both players start out the same and receive the same cards per round.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		Players can also play consecutively.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		After you finish your game, you can watch your opponent, leave the table or even start a new round.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		It is possible to invite other players, but opening private tables is not allowed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Rules</h3>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Solitaire</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">&nbsp;- also known as patience, is one of the most popular card games worldwide. Our variant is played as a duel between two players. Players aim to group all 54 cards in 4 sequences of cards in descending order (King - 1). Both players are issued the same card arrangement and therefore have the same chance of winning.</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">The game starts off with seven stacks of cards face-up. Extra cards form a draw pile of cards face-down. The player draws a card from the draw pile, exposes it and then attempts to place the card on one of the seven stacks. To be able to place a card on a stack, the draw card must follow the descending order of the card on top of a pile (leading card) and its colour must also oppose that of the leading card. For example - a player can only place a 7 of hearts or diamonds (red) on a pile led by a 8 of spades or clubs (black). If this is not possible, the player draws the next card from the draw pile and makes a new attempt. When the player exhausts the draw pile, the exhausted draw cards are rotated and the player may attempt to place the draw cards again. Rotation of the draw pile represents a new round. Players lose points for every new round he/she begins.</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">The aim of&nbsp;</span><b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">solitaire</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">&nbsp;is to hold the most points at the end of each game. Players can opt to end the game at any time, should he/she be unable to make any senseful move.</span></p>\r\n', '0', 2, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(39, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/payment_28_logo_90x50.png" style="width: 137px; height: 76px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Mayan Moons', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_6052" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Mayan Moons: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<br />\r\n		After starting&nbsp;<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Mayan Moon&trade;</strong>, choose the amount you wish use in the game. Then select your bet per spin and number of lines by using the &#39;+ / - &#39; symbols. Use the &#39;Start&#39; button to start each round, the &#39;Autostart&#39; button starts each round automatically, and a further click of the &#39;Autostart&#39; button ends the automatic process.<br />\r\n		&nbsp;<br />\r\n		With the &#39;Winnings&#39; button you can see your winning overview. Here you can also see the calculation of your win possibilities depending on the amount of your bet.<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Gamble</strong><br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		Double or nothing: As soon as you have won with a winning combination (see winning overview) you will see the &#39;Gamble&#39; button. With the &#39;Gamble Game&#39; you can double your Twists. Your winning odds are 50:50. If you would like to gamble, click the &#39;Gamble&#39; button to start the game. If you do not want to gamble, click the &#39;Bank&#39; button.<br />\r\n		&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Mayan Moon&trade; Feature</strong><br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		With three or more moon symbols (Scatter symbols) you win 15 free games. The moon symbols stay as the background to the reels positions they landed on during the free games. Should a sun symbol then land on one of these positions, then your stakes will be multiplied depending on how many golden suns cover a moon symbol.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Trace back the civilisations of central America and get Mayan gold fever! You will be showered with sparkling artefacts and ancient Mayan culture in&nbsp;</span><strong style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Mayan Moons<sup>TM</sup></strong><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">with 20 pay lines on 5 reels. And on top of that there is the beautiful Mayan princess who will help you to transform your valuable findings in to Twists! Also, there is a bonus game waiting for you in the moonlight which will bring you great wealth!</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">The aim of the game is to get 5 matching symbols along a pay line. All winning patterns start on the left reel and continue a long the pay line to the right. To win, the symbols must lie next to each other with no other symbols in between.</span></p>\r\n', '0', 1, '', 0, '', '', '', '', '');
