(40, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/1.png" style="width: 137px; height: 111px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Belote', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_3422" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Belote: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			How to play</h3>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			All details of how to play multiplayer games are covered in the general &lsquo;How to play&rsquo; instructions.&nbsp; In addition to the French and German card designs, you can now select the &lsquo;Traditional French&rsquo; design. The selection can be made in the lobby via the settings symbol. The &lsquo;Traditional French&rsquo; set was designed by&nbsp;<a href="http://svg-cards.sourceforge.net/" style="color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">David Bellot&nbsp;</a>as a vector graphic and published under the GNU Lesser General Public License&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			When beginning a new game, the player can choose whether the game is played with or without declarations.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			<b>Rules</b></h4>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Belote is a card game for 4 players and is played with a deck of 32 cards.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The players facing each other form the two teams. The order of player is anti-clockwise.&nbsp;The aim of the game is to be on the team to reach the points total first (501 points in Belote Classic, 701 in Contrée).</p>\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Trump Selection (Belote Classic)</h4>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			In order to determine the trump suit, each player receives 5 cards. The next card from the deck is placed face-up in the middle of the table. The forehand must then choose to take the card or not. If the forehand passes, the next players take it in turns to take the card or pass. If a player decides to accept the card, the suit of the card becomes the trump suit. If none of the players wish to take the card, a second round follows, whereby the players can call for the desired trump suit. If a player calls, he/she must take the card in the centre of the table. If none of the players call, the cards are reshuffled and a new round begins. The player after the forehand becomes the new forehand.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Once a trump suit is selected, each player is dealt 3 additional cards. The player, who took the card from the centre of the table, receives just two extra cards, meaning that every player has a total of 8 cards.</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Belote</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">&nbsp;is a 4 player card game which is played in teams. Players may choose between Belote Classic (without declarations) and the variant Contrée. At the start of the game the trump suit must be chosen. Players must follow suit and take tricks when possible. The highest trump card wins the trick. If no trump is played, the highest card of the played suit wins the trick.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">In the&nbsp;</span><b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Belote</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">&nbsp;Classic variant players may call &lsquo;sequences&rsquo; or &lsquo;fours&rsquo; during the first trick. If a player holds the trump Queen and the trump King, he/she can call &lsquo;Belote&rsquo;, for which he/she receive 20 bonus points. The points from the tricks and calls are totalled up for each team. The team to reach 501 or 701 points first wins the game.</span></p>\r\n', '0', 2, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(41, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/4882-featurebox_register.jpg" style="width: 214px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Backgammon', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_3331" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Backgammon: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			How to play</h3>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The Backgammon lobby is different to&nbsp;the others on the platform&nbsp;in that&nbsp;players can use tabs to&nbsp;switch between the Beginners&#39; room, the Professionals&#39; room&nbsp;and the Tournament&nbsp;room. The &quot;Tournament&quot; tab only appears when a tournament is&nbsp;due to take place. The player can use a drop-down menu to select which tables are shown: all tables or only table with free seats.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			A number of important buttons are displayed above the tabs: the settings button (to change the board settings) as well as the button to toggle the game sounds. Next to these is the question mark button, which explains the symbols, and the leave button.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Under the list of the players in the lobby are the familiar buttons: &quot;Player Info.&quot;, &quot;Ignore&quot;, &quot;Add Friend&quot; and &quot;Invite&quot;.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			A new game can be opened by clicking the button &ldquo;New Game&ldquo;. A player can select the maximum skill level of his/her opponent, in addition to other settings. A player can also choose to participate in a game which another player has already opened.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			When opening or joining a game, the player must select one of 3 modes or be aware of which mode the opponent has selected. The following modes are available:</p>\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			1. Quick Game</h4>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			In a quick game, the time limit for your move is greatly reduced. Each player is given just 30 seconds for the first move. While that move is being made, the clock shall count down. Providing the player completes his/her move within 10 seconds, an extra 10 seconds are granted for the next move (this is added to the remaining time on the clock). The maximum time limit is 30 seconds.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			For example, if a player needs 15 seconds for his/her first move, he/she shall then have just 15 seconds for&nbsp;the next move. However, should the player&nbsp;manage to complete the next move in just 5 seconds, he/she shall have 20 seconds for the next move, not 10 seconds (10 seconds of remaining time + 10 bonus seconds).</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			For quick games, it is advisable to activate the &ldquo;Automatic Roll&rdquo; function to save valuable time. For this reason, the &ldquo;Automatic Roll&rdquo; button will blink during the game until the player clicks it to activate the function. The &ldquo;Automatic Roll&rdquo; function is explained below.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Should the connection to the server be lost during a game, the rules under &ldquo;Loss of connection for multiplayer games&rdquo; take effect.</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Backgammon&nbsp;</strong>is one of the oldest board games in the world. The game consists of a board that is divided up into 4 areas: the white home board, the white outer board, the black outer board and the black home board. Each of the sections consists of 6 triangles.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Two players play the game against one another, taking turns to roll 2 six-sided dice. Each player has 15 stones, either black or white. The aim of the game is for the players to move their pieces in accordance with the result of the dice roll into their respective home boards. A stone cannot be moved to a space already occupied by more than one stone belonging to the opponent. You can, however, move a stone onto a space occupied by a single stone belonging to the opponent. Doing this leads to your opponent&rsquo;s stone being moved to the bar (the centre of the board). The opponent must bring this stone back into play before he/she can move any other stones.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Once all of your stones are in your home board, you can start to remove them from play &ndash; this is called &lsquo;bearing off&rsquo;. The first player to bear off all of his/her stones wins the game.</p>\r\n', '0', 3, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(42, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/12.jpg" style="width: 137px; height: 74px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Battlefleet', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_6123" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Battlefleet: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Start your manovers and eliminate your opponent!&nbsp; In Battlefleet you command you fleet on the playing fields which is a 10x10 grid, or in a &#39;Quick game&#39;, a 8x8 grid.&nbsp; The aim of the game is to sink the opponents battleships. Depending on the game mode, the size of the fleet, available weapons and rules of engagement vary. Prove your tactical skills by positioning your ships to fool your opponent - but most important of all: play with all guns blazing!</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n		<span style="font-size: large;"><strong style="font-style: inherit;">General instructions</strong></span><br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		You can open the game by clicking &#39;New game&#39;. At the beginning of the game its determined who can join the game and in which of the four game modes it will be played (&#39;Classic&#39;, &#39;Battle&#39;, &#39;Tactics&#39; or &#39;Quick game&#39;. Alternatively you can join another players game.<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		After starting the game the ships will be positioned. The fleet can be manually placed on the map or randomly placed by the computer (click on the little red arrow on the left under the playing field). Clicking the two crossed red arrows changes the random arrangement, and the downward pointing arrow will remove all ships from the playing field if necessary.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Take your fleet into battle and deliver your opponent to the fish! In Battlefleet sinking ships is the name of the game. Will you succeed in finding all of the enemy ships and sending them to the ocean floor? Show your tactical skills by cunningly placing your ships on the battlefield to fool your enemy and then fire those big guns. Open fire sailor!</span></p>\r\n', '0', 4, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(43, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/9.jpg" style="width: 137px; height: 74px;" /></p>\r\n', 'BloXX Duel', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_4133" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	BloXX Duel: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<p class="heading" style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n				<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Key functions</strong></p>\r\n			<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n				&rarr; &quot;Right Arrow&quot; moves&nbsp;the object to the right.&nbsp;<br />\r\n				&larr;&nbsp;&quot;Left Arrow&quot; moves the object to the left.<br />\r\n				<span style="font-family: ''’Times New Roman’''; font-size: 12pt;">&uarr;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>&quot;Up Arrow&quot; rotates the object 90 degrees clockwise.</p>\r\n			<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n				Clicking&nbsp;on the button between the two fields changes the direction of rotation.</p>\r\n			<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n				<span style="font-family: ''’Times New Roman’''; font-size: 12pt;">&darr;&nbsp;</span>The &quot;Down Arrow&quot; key makes an object fall faster.</p>\r\n			<p class="heading" style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n				The rate at which the objects fall is shown beside the&nbsp;two&nbsp;playing fields (objects/hour), as is the number of rows which still need to be completed and the object which will fall next.<br />\r\n				&nbsp;</p>\r\n			<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n				<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Rules</strong></p>\r\n			<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n				In Bloxx Duel the player must order falling blocks to form rows at the bottom of the screen. Once a row is complete it is cleared from the playing field.</p>\r\n			<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n				The object of the game is to complete 55 rows&nbsp;as quickly as possible&nbsp;and before the opponent does. The first player to win 3 rounds&nbsp;wins the game.&nbsp;</p>\r\n			<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n				The two&nbsp;playing fields&nbsp;are shown next to each other. If one player completes two rows at once, the opponent receives these rows and has to clear them from his/her playing field. The cursor/arrow keys on the keyboard&nbsp;are used to move the pieces. &quot;Up&quot; rotates the falling block 90 degrees clockwise, while &quot;Down&quot; accelerates the falling speed. &quot;Left&quot; and &quot;Right&quot; move the blocks in the corresponding direction.</p>\r\n			<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n				<b>Points</b></p>\r\n			<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n				There are no points in Bloxx Duel, just wins and losses.</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;"><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;">BloXX Duel</span><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;">&nbsp;</span></b><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;">is a popular puzzle game, in which two players play against one another. The players must rotate and manoeuvre falling blocks to form complete rows, which then disappear.&nbsp;<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The aim of the game is to clear 55 rows before your opponent. However, if your opponent clears two rows simultaneously, one will be added to your screen. If your opponent clears 3 at the same time, you&rsquo;ll receive 2 and for 4 simultaneously cleared rows, you&rsquo;ll receive all 4. The game is played over a number of rounds. The first to win 3 rounds wins the game.</span></p>\r\n', '0', 4, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(44, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/payment_28_logo_90x50.png" style="width: 137px; height: 76px;" /></p>\r\n', 'competition', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_3329" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Spin7: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">How to play</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			A new game can be opened by clicking on &ldquo;New game&rdquo;. The player must then choose the maximum skill level of his/her opponent. Alternatively, the player may join a game that has already been set up by another player.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The game screen shows four coloured game cards (pink, blue, green and orange). Each of the cards is divided up into five rows of five boxes, each containing a number between 1 and 99. The player&rsquo;s next move is shown in the display bar between the game cards.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Below the game cards are two number generators, which display the numbers and jokers for each round. To the right is the &ldquo;Spin&rdquo; button (a pink button with a circular arrow), which must be pressed to generate the new numbers at the beginning of each round.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Alternatively, the play can select the &ldquo;Autospin&rdquo; function, which activates the number generators automatically after each round. This function can be selected by clicking on the &ldquo;Autospin&rdquo; button.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			There are two types of joker in the game:&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			1. The &quot;Column Joker&quot;:&nbsp;<br />\r\n			The Column Joker is shown as an arrow in the number generators. The player can use this joker to mark off any number that is in the column directly above the arrow. It is completely up to the player, which number he/she chooses from the upper or lower game card. To play the joker, the player need only click on the desired number. Once the joker has been played, the arrow in the number generators will remain still (not blinking). The number of Column Jokers varies in each round.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			2. The &quot;Free Joker&quot;:&nbsp;<br />\r\n			At the start of each round, the player has the opportunity to mark off any number of his/her choice (on any of the four game cards) by playing the Free Joker. &ldquo;Enter your Free Joker&rdquo; shall appear in the display bar between the cards at the start of each round to prompt the player to select a number. The player receives one Free Joker at the beginning of every round.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The player need only click on a number with a coloured circle around it to mark it. The number will be covered by a yellow point. This also applies when playing the jokers. If 5 numbers in a row are marked off with yellow points (horizontally, diagonally or vertically), stars will appear on the points.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The time that the player has remaining is displayed to the right of the game cards. The player has a total of 15 minutes for each game. The clock counts down continuously from the start of the game. The current points total is displayed below the time limit.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Once the player has completed all 15 rounds, the &ldquo;Leave&rdquo; button will be shown to the right of the game cards allowing the player to leave the game. Alternatively, the player may choose to watch his/her opponent by clicking the &ldquo;Watch&rdquo; button.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			To the far right of the game screen, the opponent&rsquo;s nickname is displayed in addition to the options &ldquo;Player Info.&rdquo;, &ldquo;New Friend&rdquo; and &ldquo;Ignore&rdquo; as well as the game chat function.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class="contBox" style="margin: 0px; padding: 10px;">\r\n	<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 10px; overflow: hidden;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n			<b>This Bingo variant is a numbers game for 2 players in direct competition</b>. The game is played over&nbsp;<b>15 rounds</b>. As with the original, each player is shown game cards with boxes numbered between 1 and 99.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n			The player must mark as many numbers on the cards as possible to form rows of 5 numbers (horizontally, vertically and diagonally). The players can also use the jokers made available to gain an extra advantage.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n			<b>The aim of the game&nbsp;</b>is to mark off as many of the numbers on the cards&nbsp;as possible&nbsp;and form rows by doing so (horizontally, vertically and diagonally). The<b>winner&nbsp;</b>is the player who reaches the highest point total. The game ends once the last number has been marked in the 15th round.</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '0', 4, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(45, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/game_123_logo_137x77_EN-US.png" style="width: 137px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', '4 to win', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_1219" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	4 to win: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p class="heading" style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The playing field&nbsp;consists of a grid with 42 holes. This grid consists of 7 columns and 6 rows. The computer randomly decides who may insert a playing piece into the grid first. The player must select into which column he/she wishes to insert the piece&nbsp;by clicking on the column itself. The pieces may only be inserted vertically and only one piece may be inserted at a time.</p>\r\n		<p class="heading" style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Rules</strong></p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The game is played by two players, who play against each other. At the start of the game, each player receives 21 red or yellow playing pieces.&nbsp;The players then take turns inserting their pieces.&nbsp;The object of the game is to form a row of 4 consecutive pieces of one&#39;s own colour, either vertically, horizontally or diagonally. The game is over as soon as a player achieves this.</p>\r\n		<p class="heading" style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Points</strong></p>\r\n		<p class="heading" style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			There are not points in 4 to Win, only wins and losses.</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	4 to win is a strategy game played by two players in a duel. The screen is filled with a grid that measures 7 by 6. Each player has 21 like-coloured playing pieces (either red or yellow) and must take it in turn to insert their pieces at the top of the grid.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The aim is to form a horizontal, vertical or diagonal line of 4 playing pieces. The player to achieve this first wins the game.</p>\r\n', '0', 4, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(46, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/8(1).jpg" style="width: 137px; height: 74px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Jewel Magic', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_4135" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Jewel Magic: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			How to play</h4>\r\n		The puzzle game Jewel Magic is played as a duel, i.e. two players play against each other. The players, however, need not play simultaneously, meaning one can play after his/her opponent has finished. Five different coloured jewels cover the Jewel Magic playing field at the start of the game. The aim of the game is to clear all of the dark fields under the jewels in the fewest moves possible. The position of adjacent jewels can be switched with a click of the mouse. Only moves which form a line of at least three like jewels (either horizontally or vertically) are valid. If this is achieved, the jewels and the dark fields below them are cleared. The remaining hole is filled by new jewels, which can lead to chain reactions.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Special Stone</h4>\r\n		This Special Stone explodes after three moves have been made, clearing the jewels surrounding it. Such stones appear during the course of a game. Below the playing field is a large crystal &ndash; a further Special Stone. This can be placed at any time during the game in the playing field. It will be positioned precisely where the most dark fields will be cleared once it explodes.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Compass</h4>\r\n		The compass displays the direction in which the jewels will enter the playing field. The direction changes during the game in a clock-wise motion.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Points</h4>\r\n		For every move made 100 points are deducted. Therefore the player should attempt to clear the field in the fewest moves possible. Sometimes chain reactions are caused. If a line of 4 jewels is cleared during a chain reaction, the point value increases by 1 for every further jewel cleared in the corresponding chain. A line of 3 is therefore worth 6 points instead of 3.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<ul style="margin: 1em 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px;">\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Creating a line of 3 like jewels is worth 3 points.</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Creating a line of 4 like jewels is rewarded with 4 points. If the player sets off a chain reaction following a 4 jewel combination, each chain is worth 6 points instead of 3 for the corresponding move.</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Clearing a dark field is worth 50 points.</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Using the Special Stone costs 300 points.</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				The Special Stone clears all of the surrounding jewels.</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Players who complete Jewel Magic receive the Magic Bonus of 10,000 points.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Jewel Magic</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">&nbsp;is a colourful puzzle game, which is played as a duel. Why not try it out and see if you can resist the charm of the sparkling jewels. In Jewel Magic two players always play against each other. Five differently coloured jewels are strewn across the playing field at the start of the game.</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">The aim of the game is to clear all of the dark squares in the background in the fewest moves possible. The position of adjacent jewels can be switched simply by clicking on them with the mouse. If a row of three like jewels or more is formed (horizontally or vertically), the move is valid. The jewels will disappear along with the dark squares behind them. The resulting gap will be filled by further jewels, which could lead to a chain reaction being set off.</span></p>\r\n', '0', 4, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(47, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/payment_11_logo_90x50.png" style="width: 137px; height: 79px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Jewel Magic', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_4135" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Jewel Magic: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			How to play</h4>\r\n		The puzzle game Jewel Magic is played as a duel, i.e. two players play against each other. The players, however, need not play simultaneously, meaning one can play after his/her opponent has finished. Five different coloured jewels cover the Jewel Magic playing field at the start of the game. The aim of the game is to clear all of the dark fields under the jewels in the fewest moves possible. The position of adjacent jewels can be switched with a click of the mouse. Only moves which form a line of at least three like jewels (either horizontally or vertically) are valid. If this is achieved, the jewels and the dark fields below them are cleared. The remaining hole is filled by new jewels, which can lead to chain reactions.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Special Stone</h4>\r\n		This Special Stone explodes after three moves have been made, clearing the jewels surrounding it. Such stones appear during the course of a game. Below the playing field is a large crystal &ndash; a further Special Stone. This can be placed at any time during the game in the playing field. It will be positioned precisely where the most dark fields will be cleared once it explodes.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Compass</h4>\r\n		The compass displays the direction in which the jewels will enter the playing field. The direction changes during the game in a clock-wise motion.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Points</h4>\r\n		For every move made 100 points are deducted. Therefore the player should attempt to clear the field in the fewest moves possible. Sometimes chain reactions are caused. If a line of 4 jewels is cleared during a chain reaction, the point value increases by 1 for every further jewel cleared in the corresponding chain. A line of 3 is therefore worth 6 points instead of 3.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		<ul style="margin: 1em 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px;">\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Creating a line of 3 like jewels is worth 3 points.</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Creating a line of 4 like jewels is rewarded with 4 points. If the player sets off a chain reaction following a 4 jewel combination, each chain is worth 6 points instead of 3 for the corresponding move.</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Clearing a dark field is worth 50 points.</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Using the Special Stone costs 300 points.</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				The Special Stone clears all of the surrounding jewels.</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Players who complete Jewel Magic receive the Magic Bonus of 10,000 points.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<b style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Jewel Magic</b><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">&nbsp;is a colourful puzzle game, which is played as a duel. Why not try it out and see if you can resist the charm of the sparkling jewels. In Jewel Magic two players always play against each other. Five differently coloured jewels are strewn across the playing field at the start of the game.</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">The aim of the game is to clear all of the dark squares in the background in the fewest moves possible. The position of adjacent jewels can be switched simply by clicking on them with the mouse. If a row of three like jewels or more is formed (horizontally or vertically), the move is valid. The jewels will disappear along with the dark squares behind them. The resulting gap will be filled by further jewels, which could lead to a chain reaction being set off.</span></p>\r\n', '0', 4, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(48, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/game_97_logo_137x77_EN-US.png" style="width: 137px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', 'The winner', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_1160" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Mowing Madness: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">How to play&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Simply click on &ldquo;New Game&rdquo; to start a new game, and choose, amongst other options, the maximum skill level of your opponent. Alternatively you may join a game that has been started by another player.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			This game puts you in the shoes of a groundsman, whose duty it is to mow the football pitch perched on top of a tractor. Patches of the pitch are mown by driving over them with the tractor. The tractor can be directed by using the arrow keys and made to jump by pressing the space bar.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Starting on Level 1, you must successfully mow the entire pitch before you may progress to the next. There are 3 levels in total.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Mowing Madness is a two-player duel.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			- Both players start in the same position and are subject to the same conditions.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			- Players may play consecutive games.<br />\r\n			- Once a player has completed a game, s/he may either watch his/her opponent, or leave the game and start a new game.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			- Other players may be directly invited to play a game.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Rules</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Two players play against each other in this game. At the start of the game, each player is shown the football pitch. Stepping into the shoes of the groundsman, the players must mow the pitch with a tractor, whilst two teams are playing a game of football!&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The objective of the game is to mow as much of the pitch as possible and therefore score the most points. The winner of the game is the player with the highest points total.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The game ends when the time limit is reached, or when the player has lost all of his/her lives. Each player starts with 3 lives. One life is lost if the player collides with one of the footballers. However, you may gain extra lives &ndash; see &ldquo;Points&rdquo;.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Points</strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			For every patch of grass mown you are awarded 10 points. As long as you drive in the right direction, each patch increases in value by a further point.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			But there are not only football players to be aware of - there are also devious moles intent on ruining your lovely pitch. Jump on a mole and score 100 points! Should you manage to land on more than one mole in a row, each mole will be worth an extra 100 points. Do this by jumping just before reaching the first mole and your second jump will be twice as far.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			A heart will appear after every second mole caught &ndash; collect hearts to get extra lives.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			While mowing, objects are thrown onto the pitch, such as</p>\r\n		<ul style="margin: 1em 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px;">\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Stars</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Beer Bottles</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Beer Cases</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Toilet Paper</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Flares</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">This game puts you in the shoes of a groundsman, whose duty it is to mow the football pitch perched on top of a tractor. Patches of the pitch are mown by driving over them with the tractor. The tractor can be directed by using the arrow keys and made to jump by pressing the space bar.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Starting on Level 1, you must successfully mow the entire pitch before you may progress to the next. There are 3 Levels in total. Mowing Madness is a two-player duel.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">The objective of the game is to mow as much of the pitch as possible and therefore score the most points. The winner of the game is the player who reaches the highest points total. The game ends when the time limit is reached, or when the player has lost all of his/her lives. Each player starts with 3 lives.</span></p>\r\n', '0', 1, '', 0, '', '', '', '', '');
