(49, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/game_8_logo_220x100_EN-US.png" style="width: 137px; height: 62px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Pachisi', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_1244" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Pachisi: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			A new game can be started by simply clicking &quot;New Game&quot;. The player may then define a number of settings to determine who may join the game (Any, Friends or Invited) as well as the opponents&rsquo; skill level. Alternatively, the player may join a game that has been set up by another player.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			To roll the die, the player must click on the button &quot;Roll&quot;. To move a piece, the player need only click on the desired piece itself. Alternatively, the piece can be dragged and dropped into position. The stones that can be moved in a given turn are highlighted.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Rules</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Pachisi is a board game for 2 to 4 players. Each player receives 4 playing pieces of the same colour. Each player rolls one die at the start of the game to determine who goes first (the player who rolls the highest number starts).&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Players take turns rolling and moving their pieces around the board. Players can jump over squares containing their own and other players&rsquo; pieces, but these squares are also counted as part of the move. If a player has more than one piece on the board, he or she can move any one of them.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			If a piece stops on a square containing another player&#39;s piece, the opponent&rsquo;s piece is knocked out of play and goes back to &quot;Home&quot;. However, knocking out the piece of an opponent is not mandatory. As long as there are still pieces in &quot;Home&quot;, the player has to get them out by rolling a 6. If the first square is occupied by another player&#39;s piece, it is knocked out. If the first square is occupied by one of the player&#39;s own playing pieces, this has to be moved first using the 6. If a player rolls a 6, and there are no more pieces in &quot;Home&quot;, the player can move any of his/her pieces and then roll again. If a player brings the last piece into the home stretch by rolling a 6, he/she cannot roll again.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			A player who rolls a 6 gets to roll again after moving. If the player again rolls a 6, he/she can roll again after finishing the second turn.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Once a piece has completed a circuit around the board, it can be moved onto the squares of the same colour on the home stretch. These squares are also counted individually. If there are already pieces on the home stretch, it is possible to &lsquo;jump&rsquo; over them.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			If a player has no more pieces in play because they have all been knocked out and sent back to &quot;Home&quot;, the player is allowed to roll 3 times. This also applies if one or more pieces are on the home stretch, but only if these cannot be moved any further.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The first player to get all 4 pieces on the squares of the home stretch wins. The other players continue playing for 2nd and 3rd place.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Points</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			There are no points involved in this game. Only the result of the game, i.e. who won/lost, is important.</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Pachisi&nbsp;</strong>is a board game played around the world and is also known as &ldquo;Ludo&rdquo;. The game can be played by 2 to 4 players, who play against one another. Each player begins with four playing pieces of the same colour.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The aim of the game is to move your own pieces from the start to the end of the board by taking turns in rolling the dice. A turn consists of rolling the dice and moving the pieces around the board by the number of spaces shown on the dice.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	To bring a playing piece into play a player must roll a 6. If a player rolls a 6, he/she may roll again. If a player has no pieces on the board, he/she may roll three times. Players may jump over their own and their opponents&rsquo; pieces, however this space still counts as one of the spaces to be moved. If your piece lands on a space occupied by an opponent&rsquo;s piece, you may knock this piece all of the way back to the start. The first player to move all of his/her pieces into the home stretch is the winner</p>\r\n', '0', 6, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(50, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/4973-featurebox_twists-shop.jpg" style="width: 137px; height: 49px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Battlefleet', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_6123" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Battlefleet: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Start your manovers and eliminate your opponent!&nbsp; In Battlefleet you command you fleet on the playing fields which is a 10x10 grid, or in a &#39;Quick game&#39;, a 8x8 grid.&nbsp; The aim of the game is to sink the opponents battleships. Depending on the game mode, the size of the fleet, available weapons and rules of engagement vary. Prove your tactical skills by positioning your ships to fool your opponent - but most important of all: play with all guns blazing!</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n		<span style="font-size: large;"><strong style="font-style: inherit;">General instructions</strong></span><br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		You can open the game by clicking &#39;New game&#39;. At the beginning of the game its determined who can join the game and in which of the four game modes it will be played (&#39;Classic&#39;, &#39;Battle&#39;, &#39;Tactics&#39; or &#39;Quick game&#39;. Alternatively you can join another players game.<br />\r\n		<br />\r\n		After starting the game the ships will be positioned. The fleet can be manually placed on the map or randomly placed by the computer (click on the little red arrow on the left under the playing field). Clicking the two crossed red arrows changes the random arrangement, and the downward pointing arrow will remove all ships from the playing field if necessary.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Take your fleet into battle and deliver your opponent to the fish! In Battlefleet sinking ships is the name of the game. Will you succeed in finding all of the enemy ships and sending them to the ocean floor? Show your tactical skills by cunningly placing your ships on the battlefield to fool your enemy and then fire those big guns. Open fire sailor!</span></p>\r\n', '0', 6, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(51, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/8.jpg" style="width: 137px; height: 74px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Pressing', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_1160" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Mowing Madness: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">How to play&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Simply click on &ldquo;New Game&rdquo; to start a new game, and choose, amongst other options, the maximum skill level of your opponent. Alternatively you may join a game that has been started by another player.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			This game puts you in the shoes of a groundsman, whose duty it is to mow the football pitch perched on top of a tractor. Patches of the pitch are mown by driving over them with the tractor. The tractor can be directed by using the arrow keys and made to jump by pressing the space bar.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Starting on Level 1, you must successfully mow the entire pitch before you may progress to the next. There are 3 levels in total.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Mowing Madness is a two-player duel.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			- Both players start in the same position and are subject to the same conditions.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			- Players may play consecutive games.<br />\r\n			- Once a player has completed a game, s/he may either watch his/her opponent, or leave the game and start a new game.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			- Other players may be directly invited to play a game.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Rules</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Two players play against each other in this game. At the start of the game, each player is shown the football pitch. Stepping into the shoes of the groundsman, the players must mow the pitch with a tractor, whilst two teams are playing a game of football!</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_1160" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Mowing Madness: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">How to play&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Simply click on &ldquo;New Game&rdquo; to start a new game, and choose, amongst other options, the maximum skill level of your opponent. Alternatively you may join a game that has been started by another player.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			This game puts you in the shoes of a groundsman, whose duty it is to mow the football pitch perched on top of a tractor. Patches of the pitch are mown by driving over them with the tractor. The tractor can be directed by using the arrow keys and made to jump by pressing the space bar.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Starting on Level 1, you must successfully mow the entire pitch before you may progress to the next. There are 3 levels in total.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Mowing Madness is a two-player duel.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			- Both players start in the same position and are subject to the same conditions.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			- Players may play consecutive games.<br />\r\n			- Once a player has completed a game, s/he may either watch his/her opponent, or leave the game and start a new game.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			- Other players may be directly invited to play a game.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Rules</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Two players play against each other in this game. At the start of the game, each player is shown the football pitch. Stepping into the shoes of the groundsman, the players must mow the pitch with a tractor, whilst two teams are playing a game of football!</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '0', 6, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(52, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/10.jpg" style="width: 137px; height: 74px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Pachisi', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_1244" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Pachisi: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			A new game can be started by simply clicking &quot;New Game&quot;. The player may then define a number of settings to determine who may join the game (Any, Friends or Invited) as well as the opponents&rsquo; skill level. Alternatively, the player may join a game that has been set up by another player.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			To roll the die, the player must click on the button &quot;Roll&quot;. To move a piece, the player need only click on the desired piece itself. Alternatively, the piece can be dragged and dropped into position. The stones that can be moved in a given turn are highlighted.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Rules</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Pachisi is a board game for 2 to 4 players. Each player receives 4 playing pieces of the same colour. Each player rolls one die at the start of the game to determine who goes first (the player who rolls the highest number starts).&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Players take turns rolling and moving their pieces around the board. Players can jump over squares containing their own and other players&rsquo; pieces, but these squares are also counted as part of the move. If a player has more than one piece on the board, he or she can move any one of them.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			If a piece stops on a square containing another player&#39;s piece, the opponent&rsquo;s piece is knocked out of play and goes back to &quot;Home&quot;. However, knocking out the piece of an opponent is not mandatory. As long as there are still pieces in &quot;Home&quot;, the player has to get them out by rolling a 6. If the first square is occupied by another player&#39;s piece, it is knocked out. If the first square is occupied by one of the player&#39;s own playing pieces, this has to be moved first using the 6. If a player rolls a 6, and there are no more pieces in &quot;Home&quot;, the player can move any of his/her pieces and then roll again. If a player brings the last piece into the home stretch by rolling a 6, he/she cannot roll again.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			A player who rolls a 6 gets to roll again after moving. If the player again rolls a 6, he/she can roll again after finishing the second turn.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Once a piece has completed a circuit around the board, it can be moved onto the squares of the same colour on the home stretch. These squares are also counted individually. If there are already pieces on the home stretch, it is possible to &lsquo;jump&rsquo; over them.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			If a player has no more pieces in play because they have all been knocked out and sent back to &quot;Home&quot;, the player is allowed to roll 3 times. This also applies if one or more pieces are on the home stretch, but only if these cannot be moved any further.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The first player to get all 4 pieces on the squares of the home stretch wins. The other players continue playing for 2nd and 3rd place.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Points</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			There are no points involved in this game. Only the result of the game, i.e. who won/lost, is important.</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Pachisi&nbsp;</strong>is a board game played around the world and is also known as &ldquo;Ludo&rdquo;. The game can be played by 2 to 4 players, who play against one another. Each player begins with four playing pieces of the same colour.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The aim of the game is to move your own pieces from the start to the end of the board by taking turns in rolling the dice. A turn consists of rolling the dice and moving the pieces around the board by the number of spaces shown on the dice.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	To bring a playing piece into play a player must roll a 6. If a player rolls a 6, he/she may roll again. If a player has no pieces on the board, he/she may roll three times. Players may jump over their own and their opponents&rsquo; pieces, however this space still counts as one of the spaces to be moved. If your piece lands on a space occupied by an opponent&rsquo;s piece, you may knock this piece all of the way back to the start. The first player to move all of his/her pieces into the home stretch is the winner</p>\r\n', '0', 6, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(53, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/game_97_logo_137x77_EN-US.png" style="width: 137px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Fruits’n Sevens', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	&ldquo;Fruits&rsquo;n Sevens&rdquo; is a 5-line, 5-reel slot machine game featuring progressive jackpots. All wins pay from left to right.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	At this slot machine you can play with 5 paylines.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong style="font-style: inherit;">Progressive Jackpot:</strong></p>\r\n<ul style="margin: 1em 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		Fruits&#39;n Sevens has a common progressive jackpot for all stakes.</li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n		Five 7s in&nbsp;one win line triggers the jackpot. With a maximum stake, 100% of the progressive jackpot is won. For lower stakes, a corresponding share of the jackpot is won. For example: Progressive Jackpot: 10,000,&nbsp;Maximum Stake: 10 Twists, win: 10,000. Stake: 1 Twist, Win:&nbsp;1,000.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">In this slot machine it&rsquo;s not the cheeky fruits that call the shots &ndash; that&rsquo;s your job! Spin the reels and hit five lucky 7s &ndash; then nothing will stand between you and the Twist Jackpot!</span></p>\r\n', '0', 6, '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(54, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/flash_game/assets/flashgame/upload/images/game_49_logo_220x100_EN-US.png" style="width: 169px; height: 77px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Poker', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 id="a_1913" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Poker: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<h3 style="margin: 38px -1px 31px -12px; padding: 0px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			How to play</h3>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The Poker lobby is different to the other lobbies on the platform.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The player has the option of choosing between the games Texas Hold&rsquo;Em, Omaha&nbsp;and 5-Card Draw. Once the chosen tab has been clicked on, the open gaming tables in this area will be displayed. Only the tables open in this area will be shown, not the other area.</p>\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Player credit</h4>\r\n		<ul style="margin: 1em 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px;">\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				To begin with, each player receives a credit of 1600 chips.</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				In the game, the player may take any desired amount of these 1600 chips to the table. Should the player run out of chips during a game, he/she may use the &ldquo;Top Up Chips&rdquo; button to bring another amount of chips to the table from those still available.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			<strong style="font-style: inherit;">The games that have already been opened are shown in the lobby with the following information:</strong></p>\r\n		<ul style="margin: 1em 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px;">\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Name of the player</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Poker variant</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Stake</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Number of players already in the game</li>\r\n			<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px -11px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 16px; list-style: outside; background-image: url(http://static2.greentube.com/xsl_gamebase/_gametwist_2010/imgs/bullet_gametwist.png); background-attachment: scroll; background-color: transparent; background-position: 0px 4px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n				Maximum number of players that may take part</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			By clicking on the game, the names of the players already in the game are highlighted on the left-hand side of the lobby. To enter the game, the player can either double click on the game, or click on the &ldquo;To The Table&rdquo; button.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			To begin a new game, the player must click on &ldquo;New Table&rdquo; at the bottom of the lobby. The player must then select the limit type (No Limit, Pot Limit or Fixed Limit), the maximum number of players (Texas Hold&#39;Em: 2 to 10, 5 Card Draw: 2 to 5) and the stake (Stake Sum, Raise Sum, Limit, Small and Big Blind). Clicking on &ldquo;OK&rdquo; confirms the settings and takes the player to the game room.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The game room centres around an oval table surrounded by 10 seats. Irrespective of how many players will contest the game, each seat is marked with a yellow spot. The player can choose his/her seat by clicking one of the yellow balls, which will be replaced by a small box containing the name of the player, the player&rsquo;s credit and the current activity (&ldquo;Taking a Seat&ldquo;, &ldquo;Joining&ldquo;). The player&rsquo;s cards and the stake are displayed above this box. Once the player places a stake, the chips are shown on the table. There is also a red area on the table, which represents the pot. The figure shown is the amount currently in the pot.</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Anyone can try his/her hand at&nbsp;<strong>Poker</strong>. So why not have a crack at the world&rsquo;s most popular card game. At GameTwist you can choose from the following variants:&nbsp;<strong>Texas Hold&rsquo;Em, Omaha &amp; 5 Card Draw</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Up to 10 players may play at a single Poker table and all pay into a common pot. The player with the best hand wins the pot (stakes). There is no fixed number of rounds and each player can play at his/her own discretion. At the start of a round each player receives 2 cards. He/she must then decide whether the cards form a good foundation on which to build a hand.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Every player can match the previous bet, raise or fold. At the end of the round the player with the best hand wins the pot and a new round begins. A round consists of 4 betting rounds. Depending on the variant played, the players have various opportunities to build their hands.</p>\r\n', '0', 6, '', 0, '', '', '', '', '');

